ads.author: David Bolton
ads.title: Pinball machine Hokus Pokus 1975 owned since 1979
ads.description:
Had every switch , blade and contact filed and cleaned  and machine shopped out in 2021 by Terri Irwin , a long time respected pinball mechanic in Ocala. 
Has a few lights out. 
Only issue is sometimes the score reel does not completely set over and you have to hit the button again to restart it. One of those Ghost in the machine kind of things that she just couldn't figure out . I have owned this game since 1979 when I received it as a kid. 

You might have seen this up for sale in the past and then the listing disappeared. This was a period of time when I needed money for something so I put it up for sale but then something else came through and I took it down because I didn't really want to sell it. At this point in life it is mostly just nostalgia. I just don't play it anymore. It is very fun game I am just bored with it after 45 years and want something different.  

Very open to trades for a newer pinball machine plus cash on my end. 

Thanks for looking! 

Nine zero four four four four one four three nine.. Dave

ads.author: Donald Hopkins
ads.title: Bally Spectrum Pinball - Restored & Rare
ads.description:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AWB92q7rrVQ

I purchased this game on 1/1/2023. It was meticulously restored by Frank W. in Alabama. Fully LED'ed. All of the playfield inserts were swapped to yoppsicles making this game a maintenance dream. No more flaky bulb sockets.

I installed an aftermarket squawk and talk board made by Jeff Klein. It is leaps and bounds better than the original.

Bally supposedly made about 900 of these in 1982. But if you listen to interviews of the guys who were there back in the day (Todd Tuckey & Alan Reisman), about 300 of these games were actually sold. Operators didn't want the Spectrum because it wasn't making much money. The gameplay was just too different back then so it didn't catch on. However, 43 years later... the very unusual rules, unique gameplay and rarity have made Bally Spectrum very sought after.

This is one of the finer examples of this game you will find for sale. Priced accordingly. No excuses or issues. Plug N play.

ads.title: Skee-Ball machine. Made in America.
ads.description:
This skee-ball machine was originally purchased in Oklahoma and came with us when we moved here. Now my kids are into other things and this machine isn\u2019t used nearly as much as it should. So we\u2019ve decided to sell it. This would make an incredible addition to any game or rec room! I can remember wanting to play only this game at the arcade as a kid and this feels almost identical to the big commercial ones. Despite its size it\u2019s very easy to move and I have moved it myself without difficulty. It easily breaks down in two pieces with 4 bolts. It comes with the 4 original solid wood balls. Multiple game modes are programmed in (I\u2019ve always been a fan of the classic mode). Volume can be controlled and multi-players up to 4 as well. Don\u2019t miss out. These don\u2019t come up very often!!!
Measurements are in the pictures as well but measures 
9\u2019 overall length, 
2\u2019 in width
64\u201d at its highest point. 
I\u2019m going to add that this is not a commercial version. This is a smaller residential version. I have the measurements on here so you can mock it up to get an idea for its size. If you\u2019re looking for the same thing as what\u2019s at a Dave and busters this is not that. This is probably 1/2 to 2/3 the size of the commercial version.
Knew this machine is more than 4k. Here is the website for more information

Step into racing history with this original Pole Position upright cabinet \u2014 one of the most iconic arcade racers ever made. Released in 1982 by Atari/Namco, Pole Position was a groundbreaking driving simulator that set the standard for racing games. It\u2019s widely recognized as one of the Top 50 most historically important video games of all time.
Condition:
- Cabinet is very old and needs some love.
- Boards need work and likely new caps.
- Monitor does not power on.
- Lights come on.
- No sound currently.
- This is a project cabinet \u2014 perfect for restoration enthusiasts or collectors.
Highlights:
- Classic upright racer with simulator-style gameplay.
- Rare piece of arcade history from the golden age.
- Great candidate for restoration or display in a collection.
Important:
- Price is negotiable, but only slightly.
- Sold as-is.
- Serious buyers only.

ads.title: Pac land arcade machine
ads.description:
Needs some ajusting to the picture but other than that it works grate!
Excellent condition !!!

A cute game where Pac-Man, having arms, legs and a face, travels through scrolling cartoon worlds avoiding obstacles in a quest to help a lost fairy get home. Ghosts chase him on pogo sticks and in cars, aeroplanes and flying saucers. Hidden bonuses include fruit, flying boots, etc.

Pac-Land was produced by Bally Midway in 1984.

Bally Midway released 96 machines in our database under this trade name, starting in 1980. Bally Midway was based in United States.

Other machines made by Bally Midway during the time period Pac-Land was produced include: E2088, Gold Ball, Grand Slam (4 player version), Domino Man, Discs Of Tron, Granny and the Gators, Black Pyramid, Ten Pin Champ, Spy Hunter, and Kings of Steel

ads.author: Tom Grizzard
ads.title: 1978 Bally PLAYBOY pinball machine -New Playfield, new cabinet decals
ads.description:
Experience nostalgia with this classic 1978 Bally PLAYBOY pinball machine. This machine has been given a new lease of life with a brand new playfield and cabinet decals, making it the perfect addition to any arcade or pinball collection. The machine boasts the iconic PLAYBOY branding and provides endless hours of entertainment for all ages. Don't miss out on the chance to own this timeless piece of gaming history.

Notable Features:     Flippers (2), Pop bumpers (3), Slingshots (2), Standup targets (6), 5-bank drop targets (1), Star rollover (1), Upper left kickback lane (the Grotto).

The backglass depicts Hugh Hefner with 1976 Playmate Patti McGuire and 1977 Playmate Sondra Theodore. Tom Nieman, VP of Marketing for Bally Pinball, told us his name or initials appeared on most backglasses of this time period for which he obtained the license. On this game, his name appears on the champagne bottle.

The start-up tune, Grotto tune, and bonus score countdown tune resemble portions of Cy Coleman's "Playboy's Theme" from the 1969 TV show "Playboy After Dark". An article in the Spring 2019 issue of Playboy magazine about the "Singing Playmates" mentioned that their producer Vic Caesar "arranged the surprisingly famous theme to the Playboy pinball game."

Good condition. Everything works.

 
Will ship via freight carrier at buyer's expense... contact for quote.  Local delivery available for a nominal fee.

ads.title: Golden Tee Go v2 (2024)
ads.description:
The Golden Tee Go v2 Edition is a highly sought-after addition to any arcade gaming collection. With 54 courses and online play capabilities, this 2024 release from It Games offers an immersive gaming experience for enthusiasts. Featuring the original Golden Tee Home Edition game title, this reproduction provides a nostalgic and exciting gameplay for collectors and gaming enthusiasts alike.

Game features Standard (1 - 4 multiplayer), Closest To The Pin (1 - 4 multiplayer), Skins (1 - 4 multiplayer), & Online (1 - 4 multiplayer with activation) modes. Online Manual available upon request.

Connects directly to any standard display or TV using HDMI cable (not included).

Trackball in working condition, recommended that it be changed in near future due to dust collecting around trackball bearings from storage. 

Priced at $3200, will consider offers
